claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table listing four types of influenza vaccines (egg-based IIV4s, ccIIV4, RIV4, LAIV4) alongside their contraindications and precautions. The table only details contraindications and precautions for different influenza vaccine types; it does not discuss mutations during production or any impact on vaccine effectiveness, and thus does not support the claim.
